THE Enugu East Magistrates’ Court on Thursday, remanded Martin Ogadi, 34, in a correctional facility for alleged stealing and attempted murder. The Magistrate, Mrs Uche Mogbo, remanded the defendant, saying her court lacked jurisdiction to entertain the matter. She, however, ordered the prosecution to send the case file to the state Director of Public Prosecutions (DPP) for advice. She adjourned the case to Nov 22 to await the DPP’s advice. ALSO READ:  Boko Haram: South West governors should buckle up —Gani Adams FRSC pledges to enforce rules to curtail road traffic… Anambra needs governors with developmental ideas ― Ezeemo NIMASA donates educational materials to 4 schools in… W/African FIUs forum moves office to Nigeria Earlier, the Prosecutor, ASP Reuben Ihejiobi, told the court that the matter was reported at Abakpa Police Station on Oct. 22 by the Complainant, Mrs Grace Okoh. He told the court the defendant, who hails from Enugu East Local Government Area, allegedly stole N257,000 cash, goods worth N45,000 from Silver and Gold Hotel, Abakpa Nike and attempted to kill the Complainant, Okoh, with a wooden pestle. Ihejiobi alleged that the defendant also stole a mobile cell phone worth N36,000; MB3 worth N3,000; a male shirt worth N6,000; and another phone which price was still unknown from the hotel. He said the defendant also allegedly attempted to kill the complainant, hitting both her head and mouth with a wooden pestle, causing her grievous injuries. According to the prosecutor, the offences committed by the defendant are punishable under Sections 353 and 275 of the Criminal Code, Cap 30, VOL. II Revised Laws of Enugu State of Nigeria 2004. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
